9834e2df05fc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["September cohort", "Subsubsection"],
 "\n\nYou should expect some overlapping between this course with the \
previous course of Wolfram and and the following courses. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.778568373771381*^9, 3.778568459802706*^9}, {
   3.778568494486559*^9, 3.778568694219002*^9}, {3.778568759417004*^9, 
   3.778568986734955*^9}, {3.806134812310089*^9, 3.806134826896632*^9}, {
   3.8061348849702673`*^9, 3.806134893009139*^9}, {3.811605105359941*^9, 
   3.811605153531496*^9}, 3.9461133163199453`*^9, {3.946113456044467*^9, 
   3.946113478787813*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"130a2636-1124-46b1-b1cc-\
3b144d60a1cf"],

Cell["\<\
you will have already taken PX5007 (Programming), PX5026 (Python & R), PX5019 \
(Data Visualization), and PX5023 (Image analysis). You should expect some \
overlapping with the topics of accessing, analysing and visualizing the data, \
and have a good knowledge of the Wolfram data structures. However, several of \
these topics will be given a more deep treatment, in particular into the data \
structure and pre-processing. Notice that you should not expect this overlap \
again, so it is your chance to solidify your learning in these concepts . \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.778568373771381*^9, 3.778568459802706*^9}, {
  3.778568494486559*^9, 3.778568694219002*^9}, {3.778568759417004*^9, 
  3.778568990434648*^9}, {3.778569051374667*^9, 3.778569070982654*^9}, {
  3.946113490107689*^9, 
  3.94611368807519*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a066efb5-1d71-47bc-aad6-\
e0a1a56e3ead"],

Cell["\<\
This course will prepare you well for PX5510 (Statistics) and PX5509 (Machine \
Learning). You should expect some basic overlapping with descriptive \
statistics and time-series analysis, since these are also necessary to \
explore, characterize and pre-process the data. Also, a small overlap into \
the Machine Learning course. \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.778568373771381*^9, 3.778568459802706*^9}, {
  3.778568494486559*^9, 3.778568694219002*^9}, {3.778568759417004*^9, 
  3.77856903598446*^9}, {3.778569079510238*^9, 3.778569098563826*^9}, {
  3.811575714688798*^9, 3.811575788856749*^9}, {3.9461137034441843`*^9, 
  3.94611378278985*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"65bfa71e-90b1-4a58-aec5-\
95eca6819828"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["January Cohort", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.946113823026561*^9, 
  3.9461138334612617`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"89960513-2494-47cc-ae4f-\
0818d9fd1faa"],

Cell["\<\
You will be taken PX5007 (Programming) together with our course. The first 2 \
weeks requires no programmatic knowledge, so, by the third week you should \
have already been introduced Wolfram from PX5007. Whereas PX5007 will go on \
programmatic techniques, this course will focus on pre-processing, analysis \
and visualization.   \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.778568373771381*^9, 3.778568459802706*^9}, {
  3.778568494486559*^9, 3.778568694219002*^9}, {3.778568759417004*^9, 
  3.778568990434648*^9}, {3.778569051374667*^9, 3.778569070982654*^9}, {
  3.946113490107689*^9, 3.94611368807519*^9}, {3.946113883480571*^9, 
  3.946114050239431*^9}, {3.9461140854225063`*^9, 
  3.9461140857673807`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"acb87adc-f625-4e38-ac11-\
2c7c0a6a25f3"],

Cell["\<\
This course will prepare you well for PX5510 (Statistics) and PX5509 (Machine \
Learning), as well as PX5019 (Data Visualization), and PX5023 (Image \
analysis). You should expect some basic overlapping with descriptive \
statistics and time-series analysis, since these are also necessary to \
explore, characterize and pre-process the data. Also, a small overlap into \
the Machine Learning course. \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.778568373771381*^9, 3.778568459802706*^9}, {
  3.778568494486559*^9, 3.778568694219002*^9}, {3.778568759417004*^9, 
  3.77856903598446*^9}, {3.778569079510238*^9, 3.778569098563826*^9}, {
  3.811575714688798*^9, 3.811575788856749*^9}, {3.9461137034441843`*^9, 
  3.94611378278985*^9}, {3.946114064687066*^9, 
  3.946114072736948*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"46af878c-8f0d-49d7-a74a-\
79f724e2b7ff"],

