  3.811841162738076*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6da1dc51-204c-43a1-9583-\
cfca1699ad08"],

Cell["\<\
Blackwell Book Shop, usually with discount: INTRODUCTION TO DATA SCIENCE \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808549465569303*^9, 3.808549498529598*^9}, {
  3.883201861069903*^9, 3.883201882202429*^9}, {3.9052335277594213`*^9, 
  3.90523353467836*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cb338aab-d020-400a-a343-\
1d63d9fb174f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
There is not a single set textbook for this course, but an essential book is \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]A Hands-On Introduction to Data Science\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], by Chirag Shah, Cambridge. The following shows \
reasons for me to adopt this book:\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
   3.811576270387297*^9, 3.811576319163804*^9}, {3.811576558716316*^9, 
   3.811576563845481*^9}, {3.811576784875785*^9, 3.811576799893407*^9}, {
   3.8115790806186533`*^9, 3.811579168592494*^9}, 3.883135868739814*^9, {
   3.883136107759254*^9, 3.883136133150496*^9}, {3.905233554786327*^9, 
   3.905233556855659*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"caf61f0e-8a05-4556-8b68-\
369aa3f8c1f0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Chapter 1",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " of the book provides a good structure for understanding globally what data \
science is, and will serve as a reference for our ",
 StyleBox["Lecture 1",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". "
}], "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
  3.811576270387297*^9, 3.8115763519735317`*^9}, {3.811577691128665*^9, 
  3.811577723061118*^9}, {3.811577759431953*^9, 3.811577783382441*^9}, {
  3.811577916653935*^9, 3.8115779493560247`*^9}, {3.811577987821318*^9, 
  3.811578023229558*^9}, {3.811578248293538*^9, 
  3.8115782738996263`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c3f1b74c-c306-4338-884e-\
bc56a57332ee"],

Cell["\<\
It starts assuming no computer language is needed to understand the book, as \
such you should not be expected to know Wolfram Lecture 1 (despite that I \
will use to work out the data).\
\>", "Subsubitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
  3.811576270387297*^9, 3.8115763519735317`*^9}, {3.811577691128665*^9, 
  3.811577723061118*^9}, {3.811577759431953*^9, 3.811577783382441*^9}, {
  3.811577916653935*^9, 3.8115779493560247`*^9}, {3.811577987821318*^9, 
  3.811578023229558*^9}, {3.811578248293538*^9, 3.811578294733469*^9}, {
  3.9461158126134863`*^9, 
  3.946115829851438*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"2c75dfca-df13-491f-b671-\
569060ae0566"],

Cell["\<\
The author is a computer scientist, and as such it adopts a strong computer \
scientist view about data science. I am a physicist, working on complex \
sciences, with plenty of experience with nonlinear time-series analysis to \
provide you with other interpretations.\
\>", "Subsubitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
  3.811576270387297*^9, 3.8115763519735317`*^9}, {3.811577691128665*^9, 
  3.811577723061118*^9}, {3.811577759431953*^9, 3.811577783382441*^9}, {
  3.811577916653935*^9, 3.8115779493560247`*^9}, {3.811577987821318*^9, 
  3.811578023229558*^9}, {3.811578248293538*^9, 
  3.811578295472212*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ddb0a753-d2ff-444e-b91c-\
2fdff973a560"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The description of data types and structures in ",
 StyleBox["Chapter 2 ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "will provide a complementary reference for our ",
 StyleBox["Lecture 2",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "."
}], "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
  3.811576270387297*^9, 3.8115763519735317`*^9}, {3.811577691128665*^9, 
  3.811577723061118*^9}, {3.811577759431953*^9, 3.811577783382441*^9}, {
  3.811577916653935*^9, 3.8115779493560247`*^9}, {3.811577987821318*^9, 
  3.811578023229558*^9}, {3.811578248293538*^9, 3.811578255477157*^9}, {
  3.811578357079314*^9, 
  3.81157836387558*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9b587300-e554-4a20-bb6a-\
fa834d13a965"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Chapter 2 ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "will serve as a reference for our ",
 StyleBox["Lecture 3",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " on data pre-processing.  "
}], "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
  3.811576270387297*^9, 3.811576451214027*^9}, {3.811576517145719*^9, 
  3.811576517147863*^9}, {3.811576608189933*^9, 3.8115766520861893`*^9}, {
  3.811576726322089*^9, 3.8115767491535378`*^9}, {3.811577010779765*^9, 
  3.811577010780057*^9}, {3.811577586151924*^9, 3.811577597587715*^9}, {
  3.811577635626968*^9, 3.811577637759729*^9}, {3.8115780632424*^9, 
  3.811578072868456*^9}, {3.811578149901174*^9, 3.811578177026037*^9}, {
  3.8115782260393677`*^9, 3.8115782322370977`*^9}, {3.811578307448949*^9, 
  3.81157831198833*^9}, {3.811578342882386*^9, 3.8115783461790524`*^9}, {
  3.811578731398666*^9, 
  3.8115787337824593`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c4185e4c-b634-4ae8-b6ea-\
2b40111f2927"],

Cell["\<\
Part dedicated for data pre-processing is short, but this will be \
complemented by other literature and the vast Wolfram documentation on the \
topic. \
\>", "Subsubitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811576065424609*^9, 3.811576087676814*^9}, {
